column1: Data are reported for each calendar month. Monthly enrollment data may be updated in subsequent CMS Eligibility and Enrollment Reports. For data from June 2017 to present, several states have revised their methodology to better align with CMS Eligibility and Enrollment Reports criteria; data reported for May 2017 and earlier months were not updated to reflect this change in methodology and may not be comparable to enrollment from June 2017 forward.

The total increase in Medicaid and CHIP enrollment between the Pre-ACA Average Monthly Medicaid/CHIP Enrollment and each month reported post-ACA implementation include data only from states reporting for both periods.

For more information, please see [CMS, Medicaid and CHIP Applications, Eligibility Determinations, and Enrollment Data](http://www.medicaid.gov/medicaid-chip-program-information/program-information/medicaid-and-chip-enrollment-data/medicaid-and-chip-application-eligibility-determination-and-enrollment-data.html).

For more information on the current status of Medicaid expansion decisions, please visit the following table: [Status of State Action on the Medicaid Expansion Decision](https://www.kff.org/affordable-care-act/state-indicator/state-activity-around-expanding-medicaid-under-the-affordable-care-act/).
In addition, see the [Medicaid Enrollment and Unwinding Tracker](https://www.kff.org/medicaid/issue-brief/medicaid-enrollment-and-unwinding-tracker/) for more information on enrollment trends.

CMS, Medicaid & CHIP Monthly Applications, Eligibility Determinations, and Enrollment Reports: January 2014 - August 2024 (preliminary), as of November 27, 2024. Monthly CMS Medicaid & CHIP Enrollment Reports for all periods are available from CMS [here](http://www.medicaid.gov/medicaid-chip-program-information/program-information/medicaid-and-chip-enrollment-data/medicaid-and-chip-application-eligibility-determination-and-enrollment-data.html).

Please see full [CMS reports](http://www.medicaid.gov/medicaid-chip-program-information/program-information/medicaid-and-chip-enrollment-data/medicaid-and-chip-application-eligibility-determination-and-enrollment-data.html) for state-specific footnotes and caveats.
1. U.S. totals exclude states where data were not reported and are subject to change. The U.S. Percent change from Pre-ACA Average Monthly Enrollment also excludes these states.
2. Alabama's Pre-ACA Average Monthly Enrollment is based on one month of data, September 2013, only.
3. DC's Pre-ACA Average Monthly Enrollment includes partial-benefit enrollees and includes enrollees in other financial assistance programs who are not enrolled in Medicaid or CHIP.
4. Minnesota Pre-ACA Average Monthly Enrollment includes duplicates.
5. North Dakota's Pre-ACA Average Monthly Enrollment is based on one month of data, July 2013, only.
6. Ohio's Medicaid and CHIP data for July 2021 through the current enrollment report include individuals enrolled at any time in the month and is not a point-in-time count.
7. Oregon's Pre-ACA Average Monthly Enrollment includes emergency Medicaid population.
8. West Virginia's data includes individuals enrolled at any time in the month and is not a point-in-time count as of the last day of the reporting period.
9. Wisconsin's Pre-ACA Average Monthly Enrollment does not include retroactive enrollment.
3. Alaska data for September 2023 through February 2024 do not include all full-benefit Non-MAGI Medicaid enrollees.
4. DC's Pre-ACA Average Monthly Enrollment includes partial-benefit enrollees and includes enrollees in other financial assistance programs who are not enrolled in Medicaid or CHIP.
5. Minnesota Pre-ACA Average Monthly Enrollment includes duplicates.
6. North Dakota's Pre-ACA Average Monthly Enrollment is based on one month of data, July 2013, only.
7. Ohio's Medicaid and CHIP data for July 2021 through the current enrollment report include individuals enrolled at any time in the month and is not a point-in-time count.
8. Oregon's Pre-ACA Average Monthly Enrollment includes emergency Medicaid population.
9. West Virginia's data includes individuals enrolled at any time in the month and is not a point-in-time count as of the last day of the reporting period.
10. Wisconsin's Pre-ACA Average Monthly Enrollment does not include retroactive enrollment.
8. South Carolina's Medicaid and CHIP data for May 2021 through March 2024 include retroactive enrollments.
9. Utah data for June 2017 through May 2023 include enrollees in other financial assistance programs who are not enrolled in Medicaid or CHIP.
10. West Virginia's data includes individuals enrolled at any time in the month and is not a point-in-time count as of the last day of the reporting period.
11. Wisconsin's Pre-ACA Average Monthly Enrollment does not include retroactive enrollment.
4. Michigan data for June 2017 through May 2021 do not include all full-benefit Medicaid enrollees.
8. Utah data for June 2017 through May 2023 include enrollees in other financial assistance programs who are not enrolled in Medicaid or CHIP.
9. Washington's data for June 2017 through May 2021 includes individuals enrolled at any time in the month and is not a point-in-time count as of the last day of the reporting period.
6. Oregon's Pre-ACA Average Monthly Enrollment includes emergency Medicaid population.
7. West Virginia's data includes individuals enrolled at any time in the month and is not a point-in-time count as of the last day of the reporting period.
8. Wisconsin's Pre-ACA Average Monthly Enrollment does not include retroactive enrollment.
